title: 4 friends killed in car crash on their way to Devi Patan Temple
title_detail_value: 4 friends killed in car crash on their way to Devi Patan Temple
summary: Four friends lost their lives in a car accident after their SUV crashed into a tree near Benduli village in Gonda. They were en route to Balrampur Devipatan Temple during Navratri. Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath expressed his condolences and urged for swift relief measures. Police have started an investigation, and the victims' families have been informed.

title: UP CM Yogi Adityanath holds 'Janta Darshan' at Gorakhnath Temple
title_detail_value: UP CM Yogi Adityanath holds 'Janta Darshan' at Gorakhnath Temple
summary: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath conducted the 'Janta Darshan' programme at Gorakhnath Temple, engaging with citizens and addressing their grievances. He highlighted development under the 'double-engine govt' in Haryana, referencing the abrogation of Article 370 and promising progress without corruption ahead of the October 5 assembly elections.

title: Ayodhya gang rape: Allahabad HC bench junks Samajwadi Party man's bail plea
title_detail_value: Ayodhya gang rape: Allahabad HC bench junks Samajwadi Party man's bail plea
summary: The Lucknow bench of the Allahabad high court denied bail to Samajwadi Party's Moeed Khan, accused in the Ayodhya gang rape case, due to potential trial interference. The court emphasized timely recording of the survivor's statement and noted Moeed's high social and financial influence.

title: Varanasi Sai Baba statue row: Hindu Mahasabha spokesperson Shishir Chaturvedi arrested
title_detail_value: Varanasi Sai Baba statue row: Hindu Mahasabha spokesperson Shishir Chaturvedi arrested
summary: Akhil Bharat Hindu Mahasabha Leader Shishir Chaturvedi was arrested in Lucknow for demanding the removal of Sai Baba idols from temples. A priest claimed Chaturvedi and his supporters threatened to break the idol. This arrest led to protests by his supporters outside the police station, chanting slogans and raising tensions.

title: Lucknow's KGMU to get state-of-the-art bone marrow transplant unit
title_detail_value: Lucknow's KGMU to get state-of-the-art bone marrow transplant unit
summary: King George's Medical University in Lucknow will soon have a new Bone Marrow Transplant (BMT) unit costing Rs 2.75 crore, funded by CSR contributions. The facility will feature an 8-bed ICU with advanced equipment and specialized care for leukaemia and thalassemia patients, offering more affordable services compared to private hospitals.

title: Speeding car mows down couple in Lucknow's Thakurganj, irate locals pelt stones
title_detail_value: Speeding car mows down couple in Lucknow's Thakurganj, irate locals pelt stones
summary: A speeding car killed Ram Sahay, 55, and his wife Sarla Verma, 48, in Thakurganj on Thursday night. The couple was returning from their daughter's home when struck near Prerna Sthal on IIM Road. Authorities initiated an investigation, utilizing CCTV footage to find the driver.
